---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Base
  title="About — Statbitall"
  description="Statbitall bridges statistical theory, code implementation, and real-world decision-making."
>
  <Nav />

  <main class="about-wrapper">
    <div class="about-inner">
      <h1 class="about-heading">About Statbitall</h1>

      <div class="about-body">
        <p>
          Most statistics education splits into two unsatisfying camps: textbooks that
          prove theorems but never touch data, and tutorials that show you how to call
          <code>sklearn.fit()</code> without explaining what it's actually doing. Statbitall
          sits in the gap. Every post starts with the underlying idea, traces it to its
          mathematical foundation, implements it in code, and ends with a concrete example
          of where it matters in practice.
        </p>

        <p>
          The goal is not to make statistics easier by removing the hard parts. It's to
          make the hard parts feel inevitable — to show that the formulas aren't arbitrary,
          that the assumptions aren't bureaucratic, and that the code is just the math
          written in a different notation. If you leave a post understanding <em>why</em> a
          method works rather than just <em>how</em> to use it, that's a success.
        </p>

        <p>
          The content is organized into five modules, each covering a distinct area of
          applied statistics and machine learning:
        </p>

        <ul class="module-list">
          <li>
            <strong>Module A — Foundations.</strong> Probability, distributions, the central
            limit theorem, Bayes' theorem. The scaffolding everything else hangs on.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Module B — Inference.</strong> Hypothesis testing, t-tests, ANOVA,
            confidence intervals. How to draw conclusions from data without fooling yourself.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Module C — Supervised learning.</strong> Regression, classification,
            decision trees, ensembles. The core toolkit of predictive modeling.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Module D — Unsupervised learning.</strong> Clustering, dimensionality
            reduction, density estimation. Finding structure without labels.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Module E — Causal inference.</strong> Experiments, observational studies,
            difference-in-differences, instrumental variables. Moving from correlation to cause.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          Statbitall is written and maintained by a single person who has spent years doing
          data work in industry and keeps finding that the clearest path to better decisions
          is understanding the statistics behind the tools — not just running them.
          More posts are added as they're finished.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Base>

<style>
  .about-wrapper {
    background-color: var(--color-bg-page);
    width: 100%;
    min-height: calc(100vh - 60px);
  }

  .about-inner {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 3rem 1.25rem 4rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .about-inner {
      padding: 3rem 2rem 4rem;
    }
  }

  .about-heading {
    font-family: 'Source Serif 4', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 32px;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.3;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin: 0 0 2rem;
  }

  .about-body {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Sans', system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }

  .about-body p {
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .about-body em {
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .about-body code {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: #1B9E77;
    background-color: var(--color-border-subtle);
    padding: 2px 6px;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .module-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .module-list li {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    padding-left: 1rem;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--color-border-default);
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }

  .module-list strong {
    font-weight: 500;
  }
</style>
